consider:

1) use link headers with the response that return the list of all other
representations for the current response (work on rel values for this)

2) support for an OPTIONS call for the current URI that return the list of
possible reprsentations for the current response

3) arrange a client-drive negotiation model where the server returns 300 w/
a list of possible representations and the client picks which it wants this
time

each has pros/cons, but none of the options are dependent upon a particular
media type or canonical URI as a starting point.

hope this gives you some ideas.

